pullRequest.title: Revert open-liberty specific changes to CXF's MessageImpl object
pullRequest.bodyText: This PR reverts #11560, with the exception to some of the changes introduced to com.ibm.ws.org.apache.cxf.cxf.rt.rs.service.description.3.2.  #13209 introduced a change on top of #11560 to WadlGenerator.java, and is dependent on #11560 changes to com.ibm.ws.org.apache.cxf.cxf.rt.rs.service.description.3.2/bnd.bnd. The changes needed for #13209 were preserved.

nodes.bodyText: Can we delete this overlay file?  I think you are reverting the only Liberty-specific changes in the file.
I don't think this variable is ever used in our overlay of this file.  I think we can delete this line.
I think we can delete this overlay file too.
We can't delete this file (yet) because we still need the public MessageImpl(int isize, float factor) constructor - though I plan to contribute that back to the CXF community as soon as possible.
We can delete this overlay file - the only other changes to it have been made in CXF (and only really apply if we have the file in our source tree anyway).
I don't see where this import is used.  Maybe Eclipse added it incorrectly?
another inadvertent import? I don't see any reference to ti JAXBUtils
